Feedster now Creative Commons aware

matt

   July 20, 2003

   Feedster, the RSS search engine, now understands Creative Commons
   licenses found in feeds. This marks one of the first search engines of
   any sort to recognize our metadata and display information about it.
   They’ll start implementing them on search results and cache pages soon
   but are open to other suggestions for use.
   Category:Weblog

