Media That Matters: A CC Case Study

   2008 — 6:04 mins

   [EMBED]

   Creative Commons and Arts Engine have teamed up to create a video
   explaining how CC has helped filmmakers in the Media that Matters film
   festival.

   In this short produced by Intelligent Television, you can hear from
   established film makers on why CC is a crucial part of their work flow
   and perspective on creating new media.

Download

   Media That Matters: A CC Case Study is available in several formats:
     * h.264 M4V File (Web)
     * Ogg Theora (Web)
     * Uncompressed Quicktime (1.13gb .torrent)

Translations

   To view subtitled versions, or to contribute a translation, visit the
   dotSub page for this video.

Assets

     * Additional Video Assets
     * Transcript

License

   Creative Commons License

   Media That Matters: A CC Case Study, made in partnership with Creative
   Commons, getmiro.org, WITNESS.org and Intelligent Television, is
   licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution (CC BY) license. Please
   attribute all partners and link back to this page when providing
   attribution.

Interviews

     * Leah Sapin – Arts Engine & Media that Matters Film Festival
     * Fred Benenson – Creative Commons
     * Dean Jansen – Miro / PCF

Filmmakers

     * Grace Lile – WITNESS / The Hub
     * Jen Simmons – Bush 4 Peace
     * Niaz Mosharraf – America for Dummies
     * Jeremiah Alexis – America for Dummies
     * Elizabeth Mandel – Arctic Sun
     * Gina Telaroli – Every Third Bite

Video Production

Producer

   Intelligent Television

